      "title": "LipSync GAP Bridge",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# Geekatplay LipSync GAP Bridge\n\nUse this workflow after you already have a talking-head or face-visible source clip.\n\n**Required add-on**\n- Install `GeekatplayStudio/ComfyUI-LipSync-GAP` into `ComfyUI/custom_nodes`.\n- Run its `install.bat` so `ComfyUI/models/latentsync/latentsync_unet.pt`, the Whisper checkpoint, and `latentsync/weights/face_landmarker.task` are available.\n\n**How to use it**\n1. Load the source video in `GAPLoadVideoUI`.\n2. Load the target speech or narration in `GAPLoadAudioUI`.\n3. Select a standard SD 1.5 compatible checkpoint in `CheckpointLoaderSimple`; the workflow only uses its VAE output for the LipSync GAP loader.\n4. Tune `GapLipSyncModelLoader` precision and Whisper size if needed.\n5. Keep `frame_rate` aligned to the source clip and export with `GAPVideoExporter`.\n\nThis bridge stays separate from the LTX generation lanes on purpose. It is the post-generation stage when you need exact mouth motion rather than the lighter audio-driven LTX path."
      ],
      "color": "#323",
      "bgcolor": "#535"
    },
